    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div type="letter">
                <div type="text">
                    <opener>
                        <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent.</hi></placeName>
                        <date>May 22<hi rend="superscript">d</hi></date>
                        <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                    </opener>
                    <div type="transcription">
                        <p>I am greatly indebted to you for your kindness in sending me your Text-Book of Metoreology, which I have no doubt I shall find very useful &amp; interesting.<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
                        <p>With my best thanks, I remain | Dear Sir | Yours faithfully &amp; obliged | Charles Darwin</p>
                    </div>
                </div>                
                      
                
                
                
            </div>
            
            
            <div type="footnotes">
                <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the publication date of Buchan’s book (see n. 2, below).</note>
                <note xml:id="foot.f2">Buchan’s <hi rend="italic">Introductory text-book of meteorology</hi> (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_10980.xml">Buchan 1871</ref>) was published in June 1871 (<hi rend="italic">Publishers’ Circular</hi>, 1 July 1871, p. 402); CD evidently received a pre-publication copy.</note>
            </div>
        
